section.container#getting-started
  if (!isHome)
    include carbonads.pug
  h3.title
    | Getting Started
  p.description
    | There are some ways to get started. First, see all download options available below, then choose the most suitable option for your need. Now you should add the main file of the Milligram and the CSS Reset in the header of your project. Just that!
  p
    a.button.download(href='https://github.com/milligram/milligram/archive/master.zip' title='Download Milligram') Download Milligram
  div.example
    p
      strong Install with Bower
    p
      | Milligram is available to install using Bower.
  pre.code.prettyprint.lang-bash
    code.code-content
      | $ bower install milligram
  p
    strong Install with npm
  p
    | Milligram is also available to install using npm.
  pre.code.prettyprint.lang-bash
    code.code-content
      | $ npm install milligram
  p
    strong Install with Yarn
  p
    | Milligram is also available to install using Yarn.
  pre.code.prettyprint.lang-bash
    code.code-content
      | $ yarn add milligram
  p
    strong What's included
  p
    | Once downloaded, extract the compressed folder to see the main file in the uncompressed and minified version.
  pre.code.prettyprint.lang-md
    code.code-content
      | milligram/
      | ├── dist/
      | │   ├── milligram.css
      | │   └── milligram.min.css
      | ├── example.html
      | ├── license
      | └── readme.md
  p
    strong Usage
  p
    | First, use any method mentioned above to download Milligram. Then, just add these tags in the head. Milligram is also available via
    a(href='https://cdnjs.com/libraries/milligram' title='Milligram is also available via CDN' target='_blank' rel='noopener')  CDN
    | .
  pre.code.prettyprint.lang-html
    code.code-content
      | /* Google Fonts */
      | <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto:300,300italic,700,700italic">
      = '\n\n'
      | /* CSS Reset */
      | <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/normalize/8.0.1/normalize.css">
      = '\n\n'
      | /* Milligram CSS */
      | <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/milligram/1.4.1/milligram.css">
      = '\n\n'
      | /* You should properly set the path to /dist/milligram.min.css if you installed it with a package manager. */
  p
    strong CLI
  p
    | A CLI for getting started with Milligram. It offers a super simple boilerplate project with Milligram.
  pre.code.prettyprint.lang-bash
    code.code-content
      | $ npm install -g milligram-cli
  p
    | Create a new app using the command
    = ' '
    code
      | milligram init
    |, then install dependencies and run with
    = ' '
    code
      | npm start
    | .
  pre.code.prettyprint.lang-bash
    code.code-content
      | $ milligram init new_app
      | $ cd new_app
      | $ npm start
  if (isHome)
    p
      | See more examples of
      = ' '
      a(href='getting-started.html' title='Getting Started') getting started
      | .
